{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":878,"text":"The world is filled\nwith incredible objects"},{"time":4427,"text":"and rich cultural heritage."},{"time":7283,"text":"And when we get access to them,"},{"time":9443,"text":"we are blown away, we fall in love."},{"time":12652,"text":"But most of the time,"},{"time":14273,"text":"the world's population is living\nwithout real access to arts and culture."},{"time":19946,"text":"What might the connections be\nwhen we start exploring our heritage,"},{"time":25323,"text":"the beautiful locations\nand the art in this world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":29427,"text":"Before we get started\nin this presentation,"},{"time":32225,"text":"I just want to take care\nof a few housekeeping points."},{"time":35651,"text":"First, I am no expert in art or culture."},{"time":39023,"text":"I fell into this by mistake,\nbut I'm loving it."},{"time":42356,"text":"Secondly, all of what\nI'm going to show you"},{"time":45376,"text":"belongs to the amazing museums,\narchives and foundations"},{"time":49365,"text":"that we partner with."},{"time":50815,"text":"None of this belongs to Google."},{"time":53235,"text":"And finally, what you see behind me"},{"time":56448,"text":"is available right now\non your mobile phones,"},{"time":59823,"text":"on your laptops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61021,"text":"This is our current platform,\nwhere you can explore"},{"time":63449,"text":"thousands of museums\nand objects at your fingertips,"},{"time":66884,"text":"in extremely high-definition detail."},{"time":69419,"text":"The diversity of the content\nis what's amazing."},{"time":72336,"text":"If we just had European paintings,"},{"time":74529,"text":"if we just had modern art,"},{"time":76284,"text":"I think it gets a bit boring."},{"time":78110,"text":"For example, this month,\nwe launched the \"Black History\" channel"},{"time":81993,"text":"with 82 curated exhibitions,"},{"time":84606,"text":"which talk about arts and culture\nin that community."},{"time":88196,"text":"We also have some\namazing objects from Japan,"},{"time":91843,"text":"centered around craftsmanship,\ncalled \"Made in Japan.\""},{"time":95971,"text":"And one of my favorite exhibitions,"},{"time":99122,"text":"which actually is the idea of my talk,"},{"time":101551,"text":"is -- I didn't expect to become\na fan of Japanese dolls."},{"time":105438,"text":"But I am, thanks to this exhibition,"},{"time":108626,"text":"that has really taught me\nabout the craftsmanship"},{"time":112135,"text":"behind the soul of a Japanese doll."},{"time":114281,"text":"Trust me, it's very exciting."},{"time":116533,"text":"Take my word for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117905,"text":"So, moving on swiftly."},{"time":119938,"text":"One quick thing I wanted\nto showcase in this platform,"},{"time":122794,"text":"which you can share with your kids\nand your friends right now,"},{"time":125753,"text":"is you can travel to all these\namazing institutions virtually, as well."},{"time":130033,"text":"One of our recent ideas was with\nThe Guggenheim Museum in New York,"},{"time":133643,"text":"where you can get a taste\nof what it might feel like"},{"time":137025,"text":"to actually be there."},{"time":138200,"text":"You can go to the ground floor"},{"time":139991,"text":"and obviously, most of you,\nI assume, have been there."},{"time":142704,"text":"And you can see the architectural\nmasterpiece that it is."},{"time":145465,"text":"But imagine this accessibility\nfor a kid in Bombay"},{"time":148583,"text":"who's studying architecture,"},{"time":150327,"text":"who hasn't had a chance\nto go to The Guggenheim as yet."},{"time":153406,"text":"You can obviously look at objects\nin the Guggenheim Museum,"},{"time":156515,"text":"you can obviously get into them\nand so on and so forth."},{"time":159257,"text":"There's a lot of information here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161156,"text":"But this is not the purpose\nof my talk today."},{"time":165543,"text":"This exists right now."},{"time":167333,"text":"What we now have are the building blocks\nto a very exciting future,"},{"time":171283,"text":"when it comes to arts and culture"},{"time":173022,"text":"and accessibility to arts and culture."},{"time":175657,"text":"So I am joined today onstage\nby my good friend and artist in residence"},{"time":180149,"text":"at our office in Paris, Cyril Diagne,"},{"time":182516,"text":"who is the professor of interactive design"},{"time":184669,"text":"at ECAL University\nin Lausanne, Switzerland."},{"time":187330,"text":"What Cyril and our team\nof engineers have been doing"},{"time":189968,"text":"is trying to find these connections\nand visualize a few of these."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193127,"text":"So I'm going to go quite quick now."},{"time":194964,"text":"This object you see\nbehind me -- oh, just clarification:"},{"time":198590,"text":"Always, seeing the real thing is better."},{"time":200565,"text":"In case people think\nI'm trying to replicate the real thing."},{"time":203452,"text":"So, moving on."},{"time":205155,"text":"This object you see behind me\nis the Venus of Berekhat Ram."},{"time":208695,"text":"It's one of the oldest\nobjects in the world,"},{"time":210795,"text":"found in the Golan Heights\naround 233,000 years ago,"},{"time":213993,"text":"and currently residing\nat the Israel Museum in Jerusalem."},{"time":217146,"text":"It is also one of the oldest\nobjects on our platform."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220322,"text":"So let's zoom."},{"time":221692,"text":"We start from this one object."},{"time":223986,"text":"What if we zoomed out"},{"time":226546,"text":"and actually tried to experience\nour own cultural big bang?"},{"time":231076,"text":"What might that look like?"},{"time":233474,"text":"This is what we deal with on a daily basis\nat the Cultural Institute --"},{"time":237155,"text":"over six million cultural artifacts\ncurated and given to us by institutions,"},{"time":242141,"text":"to actually make these connections."},{"time":244111,"text":"You can travel through time,"},{"time":245534,"text":"you can understand more\nabout our society through these."},{"time":249069,"text":"You can look at it\nfrom the perspective of our planet,"},{"time":253493,"text":"and try to see how\nit might look without borders,"},{"time":256152,"text":"if we just organized art and culture."},{"time":258847,"text":"We can also then plot it by time,"},{"time":261099,"text":"which obviously, for the data geek\nin me, is very fascinating."},{"time":265203,"text":"You can spend hours\nlooking at every decade"},{"time":268613,"text":"and the contributions\nin that decade and in those years"},{"time":271953,"text":"for art, history and cultures."},{"time":274310,"text":"We would love to spend hours\nshowing you each and every decade,"},{"time":277713,"text":"but we don't have the time right now."},{"time":279598,"text":"So you can go on your phone\nand actually do it yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282881,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":286367,"text":"But if you don't mind\nand can hold your applause till later,"},{"time":289493,"text":"I don't want to run out of time,"},{"time":291065,"text":"because I want to show you\na lot of cool stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293288,"text":"So, just very quickly:"},{"time":294812,"text":"you can move on from here\nto another very interesting idea."},{"time":298822,"text":"Beyond the pretty picture,"},{"time":300557,"text":"beyond the nice visualization,"},{"time":302370,"text":"what is the purpose, how is this useful?"},{"time":304721,"text":"This next idea comes\nfrom discussions with curators"},{"time":309474,"text":"that we've been having at museums,"},{"time":311133,"text":"who, by the way, I've fallen in love with,"},{"time":313180,"text":"because they dedicate their whole life\nto try to tell these stories."},{"time":316398,"text":"One of the curators told me,\n\"Amit, what would it be like"},{"time":319353,"text":"if you could create\na virtual curator's table"},{"time":321856,"text":"where all these six million objects"},{"time":324183,"text":"are displayed in a way for us\nto look at the connections between them?\""},{"time":328610,"text":"You can spend a lot of time, trust me,\nlooking at different objects"},{"time":332663,"text":"and understanding where they come from."},{"time":334640,"text":"It's a crazy Matrix experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336872,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337910,"text":"Just moving on,"},{"time":339220,"text":"let's take the world-famous\nVincent Van Gogh,"},{"time":342415,"text":"who is very well-represented\non this platform."},{"time":346154,"text":"Thanks to the diversity\nof the institutions we have,"},{"time":348954,"text":"we have over 211 high-definition,\namazing artworks by this artist,"},{"time":354682,"text":"now organized in one beautiful view."},{"time":358453,"text":"And as it resolves,\nand as Cyril goes deeper,"},{"time":361450,"text":"you can see all the self-portraits,"},{"time":363683,"text":"you can see still life."},{"time":365132,"text":"But I just wanted to highlight\none very quick example,"},{"time":367759,"text":"which is very timely:"},{"time":369471,"text":"\"The Bedroom.\""},{"time":370806,"text":"This is an artwork\nwhere three copies exist --"},{"time":373131,"text":"one at the Van Gogh Museum in Amsterdam,"},{"time":375485,"text":"one at the Orsay in Paris"},{"time":377496,"text":"and one at the Art Institute of Chicago,"},{"time":379454,"text":"which, actually, currently\nis hosting a reunion"},{"time":381981,"text":"of all three artworks physically,"},{"time":383780,"text":"I think only for the second time ever."},{"time":385941,"text":"But, it is united digitally and virtually\nfor anybody to look at"},{"time":390884,"text":"in a very different way,"},{"time":392829,"text":"and you won't get pushed\nin the line in the crowd."},{"time":395886,"text":"So let's take you and let's travel\nthrough \"The Bedroom\" very quickly,"},{"time":400652,"text":"so you can experience what we are doing\nfor every single object."},{"time":404263,"text":"We want the image to speak\nas much as it can"},{"time":407738,"text":"on a digital platform."},{"time":409406,"text":"And all you need is an internet\nconnection and a computer"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412577,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":416939,"text":"And, Cyril, if you can go deeper, quickly."},{"time":419521,"text":"I'm sorry, this is all live,"},{"time":421029,"text":"so you have to give Cyril\na little bit of --"},{"time":424401,"text":"and this is available for every object:"},{"time":426485,"text":"modern art, contemporary art,\nRenaissance -- you name it,"},{"time":429224,"text":"even sculpture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431802,"text":"Sometimes, you don't know\nwhat can attract you"},{"time":435421,"text":"to an artwork or to a museum\nor to a cultural discovery."},{"time":440673,"text":"So for me, personally,\nit was quite a challenge"},{"time":443439,"text":"because when I decided to make this\nmy full-time job at Google,"},{"time":446685,"text":"my mother was not very supportive."},{"time":449312,"text":"I love my mother,"},{"time":450583,"text":"but she thought I was wasting my life\nwith this museum stuff."},{"time":453606,"text":"And for her, a museum is what\nyou do when you go on vacation"},{"time":456942,"text":"and you tick-mark and it's over, right?"},{"time":458933,"text":"And it took around four and a half years"},{"time":461488,"text":"for me to convince my lovely Indian mother"},{"time":463726,"text":"that actually, this is worthwhile."},{"time":465403,"text":"And the way I did it was,\nI realized one day that she loves gold."},{"time":468868,"text":"So I started showing her all objects\nthat have the material gold in them."},{"time":474467,"text":"And the first thing my mom asks me is,"},{"time":477142,"text":"\"How can we buy these?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":479594,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":481436,"text":"And obviously, my salary is not that high,"},{"time":484602,"text":"so I was like, \"We can't\nactually do that, mom."},{"time":487004,"text":"But you can explore them virtually.\""},{"time":489139,"text":"And so now my mom -- every time\nI meet her, she asks me,"},{"time":492582,"text":"\"Any more gold, any more silver\nin your project? Can you show me?\""},{"time":496072,"text":"And that's the idea\nI'm trying to illustrate."},{"time":498270,"text":"It does not matter how you get in,"},{"time":500432,"text":"as long as you get in."},{"time":501818,"text":"Once you get in, you're hooked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503452,"text":"Moving on from here very quickly,"},{"time":505825,"text":"there is kind of a playful idea, actually,"},{"time":508698,"text":"to illustrate the point of access,"},{"time":510357,"text":"and I'm going to go\nquite quickly on this one."},{"time":512803,"text":"We all know that seeing the artwork\nin person is amazing."},{"time":518234,"text":"But we also know\nthat most of us can't do it,"},{"time":520841,"text":"and the ones that can afford\nto do it, it's complicated."},{"time":523623,"text":"So -- Cyril, can we load\nup our art trip, what do we call it?"},{"time":527454,"text":"We don't have a good name for this."},{"time":529240,"text":"But essentially, we have\naround 1,000 amazing institutions,"},{"time":534235,"text":"68 countries."},{"time":535426,"text":"But let's start with Rembrandt."},{"time":537150,"text":"We might have time for only one example."},{"time":539416,"text":"But thanks to the diversity,"},{"time":541669,"text":"we've got around 500 amazing\nRembrandt object artworks"},{"time":545597,"text":"from 46 institutions and 17 countries."},{"time":547890,"text":"Let's say that on your next vacation,"},{"time":550466,"text":"you want to go see\nevery single one of them."},{"time":552540,"text":"That is your itinerary,"},{"time":553898,"text":"you will probably travel\n53,000 kilometers,"},{"time":557576,"text":"visit around, I think, 46 institutions,"},{"time":560187,"text":"and just FYI, you might release\n10 tons of CO2 emissions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564402,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":565889,"text":"But remember, it's art,"},{"time":567386,"text":"so you can justify it,\nperhaps, in some way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570837,"text":"Moving on swiftly from here,"},{"time":572783,"text":"is something a little bit\nmore technical and more interesting."},{"time":575742,"text":"All that we've shown you so far\nuses metadata to make the connections."},{"time":580703,"text":"But obviously we have\nsomething cool nowadays"},{"time":582837,"text":"that everyone likes to talk about,\nwhich is machine learning."},{"time":585773,"text":"So what we thought is,\nlet's strip out all the metadata,"},{"time":588871,"text":"let's look at what machine learning can do"},{"time":592507,"text":"based purely on visual recognition\nof this entire collection."},{"time":596854,"text":"What we ended up with\nis this very interesting map,"},{"time":601071,"text":"these clusters that have\nno reference point information,"},{"time":605405,"text":"but has just used visuals\nto cluster things together."},{"time":609394,"text":"Each cluster is an art to us\nby itself of discovery."},{"time":613000,"text":"But one of the clusters we want\nto show you very quickly"},{"time":615687,"text":"is this amazing cluster of portraits"},{"time":618363,"text":"that we found from museums\naround the world."},{"time":620789,"text":"If you could zoom in\na little bit more, Cyril."},{"time":622996,"text":"Just to show you, you can\njust travel through portraits."},{"time":626852,"text":"And essentially, you can do nature,\nyou can do horses"},{"time":629650,"text":"and clusters galore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632309,"text":"When we saw all these portraits,"},{"time":633881,"text":"we were like, \"Hey, can we do\nsomething fun for kids,"},{"time":637557,"text":"or can we do something playful"},{"time":639263,"text":"to get people interested in portraits?\""},{"time":641312,"text":"Because I haven't really seen"},{"time":643516,"text":"young kids really excited\nto go to a portrait gallery."},{"time":647357,"text":"I wanted to try to figure something out."},{"time":649313,"text":"So we created something\ncalled the portrait matcher."},{"time":651804,"text":"It's quite self-explanatory,"},{"time":653145,"text":"so I'm just going to let Cyril\nshow his beautiful face."},{"time":655907,"text":"And essentially what's happening is,\nwith the movement of his head,"},{"time":660063,"text":"we are matching different portraits\naround the world from museums."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664254,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":677445,"text":"And I don't know about you,"},{"time":679175,"text":"but I've shown it to my nephew and sister,"},{"time":681215,"text":"and the reaction is just phenomenal."},{"time":683088,"text":"All they ask me is,\n\"When can we go see this?\""},{"time":687492,"text":"And by the way, if we're nice,"},{"time":689089,"text":"maybe, Cyril, you can smile\nand find a happy one?"},{"time":692696,"text":"Oh, perfect."},{"time":694118,"text":"By the way, this is not rehearsed."},{"time":696474,"text":"Congrats, Cyril. Great stuff. Oh wow."},{"time":699078,"text":"OK, let's move on; otherwise,\nthis will just take the whole time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702578,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":704320,"text":"So, art and culture\ncan be fun also, right?"},{"time":707900,"text":"For our last quick experiment --"},{"time":711321,"text":"we call all of these \"experiments\" --"},{"time":713108,"text":"our last quick experiment\ncomes back to machine learning."},{"time":716021,"text":"We show you clusters, visual clusters,"},{"time":718886,"text":"but what if we could ask the machine\nto also name these clusters?"},{"time":723811,"text":"What if it could automatically tag\nthem, using no actual metadata?"},{"time":728588,"text":"So what we have is this kind of explorer,"},{"time":732712,"text":"where we have managed to match,\nI think, around 4,000 labels."},{"time":736347,"text":"And we haven't really\ndone anything special here,"},{"time":739535,"text":"just fed the collection."},{"time":741217,"text":"And we found interesting categories."},{"time":743011,"text":"We can start with horses,\na very straightforward category."},{"time":745940,"text":"You would expect to see\nthat the machine has put"},{"time":748263,"text":"images of horses, right?"},{"time":750028,"text":"And it has, but you also notice,\nright over there,"},{"time":753494,"text":"that it has a very abstract image"},{"time":755597,"text":"that it has still managed to recognize\nand cluster as horses."},{"time":758816,"text":"We also have an amazing head\nin terms of a horse."},{"time":762530,"text":"And each one has the tags\nas to why it got categorized in this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766556,"text":"So let's move to another one\nwhich I found very funny and interesting,"},{"time":770554,"text":"because I don't understand\nhow this category came up."},{"time":773069,"text":"It's called \"Lady in Waiting.\""},{"time":774843,"text":"If, Cyril, you do it very quickly,"},{"time":777479,"text":"you will see that we have\nthese amazing images"},{"time":781045,"text":"of ladies, I guess, in waiting or posing."},{"time":783830,"text":"I don't really understand it."},{"time":785300,"text":"But I've been trying to ask\nmy museum contacts,"},{"time":787564,"text":"you know, \"What is this?\nWhat's going on here?\""},{"time":789833,"text":"And it's fascinating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791469,"text":"Coming back to gold very quickly,"},{"time":794182,"text":"I wanted to search for gold"},{"time":795769,"text":"and see how the machine\ntagged all the gold."},{"time":797895,"text":"But, actually, it doesn't tag it as gold."},{"time":800320,"text":"We are living in popular times."},{"time":801859,"text":"It tags it as \"bling-bling.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":803986,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":807200,"text":"I'm being hard on Cyril,\nbecause I'm moving too fast."},{"time":810145,"text":"Essentially, here you have\nall the bling-bling"},{"time":812796,"text":"of the world's museums organized for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815981,"text":"And finally, to end this talk\nand these experiments,"},{"time":819521,"text":"what I hope you feel after this talk\nis happiness and emotion."},{"time":822862,"text":"And what would we see\nwhen we see happiness?"},{"time":825325,"text":"If we actually look at all the objects"},{"time":828508,"text":"that have been tagged under \"happiness,\""},{"time":830476,"text":"you would expect happiness, I guess."},{"time":833564,"text":"But there was one that came up\nthat was very fascinating and interesting,"},{"time":839691,"text":"which was this artwork\nby Douglas Coupland,"},{"time":844090,"text":"our friend and artist\nin residence as well,"},{"time":846209,"text":"called, \"I Miss My Pre-Internet Brain.\""},{"time":848494,"text":"I don't know why the machine feels like\nit misses its pre-Internet brain"},{"time":852133,"text":"and it's been tagged here,"},{"time":853427,"text":"but it's a very interesting thought."},{"time":855365,"text":"I sometimes do miss my pre-Internet brain,"},{"time":857572,"text":"but not when it comes to exploring\narts and culture online."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860596,"text":"So take out your phones,\ntake out your computers,"},{"time":862933,"text":"go visit museums."},{"time":864114,"text":"And just a quick call-out\nto all the amazing archivists,"},{"time":866817,"text":"historians, curators,"},{"time":868225,"text":"who are sitting in museums,\npreserving all this culture."},{"time":871021,"text":"And the least we can do is get\nour daily dose of art and culture"},{"time":874363,"text":"for ourselves and our kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":875718,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876895,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}